Key Match Events: Kylian Mbappé scored once and added two assists in his first outing since his move to Real Madrid was announced, as France strolled to a comfortable 3-0 win over Luxembourg in a pre-Euro 2024 friendly in Metz on Wednesday.
Randal Kolo Muani scored the first goal for France at the 43rd minute.
Jonathan Clauss scored the second goal for France at the 70th minute.
Kylian Mbappé scored the third goal for France at the 85th minute.
